The Canadian Air Transport Security Authority (CATSA) has 1 (one) exciting indeterminate opportunity within the Operations branch at the CATSA Headquarters.
This position represents an opportunity for career-driven individuals seeking a position within an organization that inspires growth and promotes excellence to make a difference and contribute to CATSA’s unique culture as it strives to excel in air transport security.
Why is CATSA a great fit for you?
CATSA is world leader in aviation security and screening with a mandate to protect the public. A Crown corporation, it features a mix of public service and private sector diverse backgrounds in which is reflective of the varied background of its employees. CATSA encourages innovation and creativity and offers a healthy and diverse workplace where employees work in an environment where they can be their true selves and feel energized and proud.
If you are a motivated professional seeking a position within a multifunctional and collaborative environment and you are looking for the next great adventure, CATSA is the place for you!
Summary of responsibilities:
Reporting to the Manager, Program Innovation and Reporting , the Senior Analyst, Operations Performance is responsible for assisting in the design and development of quantitative models to assess operational performance. The Senior Analyst, Operations Performance is also responsible for providing subject matter expertise on operational data collection and reporting systems. The Senior Analyst, Operations Performance performs all other duties and responsibilities related to the position as required.
What you need to succeed:
To qualify for the position, you must have:
Graduation with a degree from a recognized university or professional college with a specialization in mathematics, economics, computer science or a related field relevant to the duties of the position;
Minimum of 5 years experience with data analysis, performance measurement methods, statistical concepts and reporting techniques; Experience drafting clear and concise reports and presentations with a strong attention to detail;
Experience researching varied and complex issues from a wide array of inputs and sources and recommending solutions;
Proficiency in the use of Microsoft Office suite of applications, particularly Excel, Word and Power Point;
Demonstrated experience analyzing business issues and providing recommendations to management;
Demonstrated ability to interpret ambiguous information and seek solutions to problems.
This position is best suited to individuals with the following skills and abilities:
Ability to multi-task and manage priorities;
Strong organizational skills;
Strong technical skills with an emphasis on analytical software;
Strong analytical skills with emphasis on quantitative analysis and a solid understanding of the principles of statistics;
Deadline and detail-oriented;
Meticulous, rigorous and thorough;
Superior skills in research, analysis and problem-solving accompanied by an ability to synthesize and interpret complex information;
Ability to understand client needs;
Ability to communicate effectively orally and in writing;
Ability to work independently as well as in a collaborative team environment.
Valuable skills include:
Experience with Access, Visio as well as Cognos suite of BI applications (or other business intelligence tools);
Experience using mathematical/statistical models and software such as SAS or SPSS;
Knowledge of mathematical and statistical theory and application;
Knowledge of the Canadian Air Transport Security Authority (CATSA) organizational structure, mandate, priorities, operating environment and its interrelationships with other internal/ external government and industry stakeholders will be considered an asset
Specific work requirements:
Must work from Ottawa head office as required;
Ability to work overtime as required;
Ability to travel as required;
Language Profile: Bilingual (BBBB)
Ability to obtain and maintain a Secret security clearance;
Be a Canadian citizen or permanent resident.
How to apply:
If you feel you are the ideal candidate for this position, please click on the following link to submit your application before April 10, 2023 by 11:59pm EST.
Additional information:
Please note that candidates that meet all the position requirements, including the language profile, will be given first consideration however, we invite all interested candidates to submit their applications;
While we appreciate all the candidates’ interest, only those being considered in the process will be contacted;
CATSA will use this opportunity to establish a candidate pool that may be used to staff permanent or fixed-term positions with similar responsibilities and qualifications;
CATSA is dedicated to an inclusive selection process and work environment. If you require an accommodation, please advise the Human Resources representative when you are invited to meet with us regarding this employment opportunity.
Inclusion & Diversity
As an employer committed to a diverse workforce, we encourage candidates in designated groups - women, visible minorities, Aboriginal persons and persons with disabilities - to apply and self-identify by answering the questions on the online application form.
